label.value: CCDC26 wt Allele

value.value: Human CCDC26 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 8q24.21 and is approximately 329 kb in length. This allele, which encodes CCDC26 long non-coding RNA and/or putative coiled-coil domain-containing protein 26, may play a role in the cellular response to retinoic acid.

label.value: Downstream Enhancer

value.value: An enhancer which is located 3' of the gene it regulates.

label.value: Putative Coiled-Coil Domain-Containing Protein 26

value.value: Putative coiled-coil domain-containing protein 26 (109 aa, ~13 kDa) is encoded by the human CCDC26 gene. This protein may play a role in the cellular response to retinoic acid.

label.value: CCDC26 Long Non-Coding RNA

value.value: CCDC26 long non-coding RNA (~1.7 kb) is encoded by the human CCDC26 gene. This long non-coding RNA may be involved in retinoic acid-mediated cellular processes.

label.value: RTEL1 Gene

value.value: This gene plays a role in telomere maintenance and the regulation of meiotic crossover recombination.

label.value: RTEL1 wt Allele

value.value: Human RTEL1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 20q13.33 and is approximately 38 kb in length. This allele, which encodes regulator of telomere elongation helicase 1 protein, is involved in telomere and chromosome maintenance. Mutation of the gene is associated with telomere-related pulmonary fibrosis and/or bone marrow failure 3 and dyskeratosis congenita types autosomal dominant 4 and autosomal recessive 5.

label.value: Regulator of Telomere Elongation Helicase 1

value.value: Regulator of telomere elongation helicase 1 (1219 aa, ~134 kDa) is encoded by the human RTEL1 gene. This protein plays a role in the maintenance of chromosomes and telomeres.

Well-differentiated neuroendocrine tumors and sarcomas are not staged using this staging system. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Gallbladder Cancer by AJCC v8 Stage

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of gallbladder cancer according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer, 8th edition. This staging system applies to gallbladder carcinomas. Well-differentiated neuroendocrine tumors and sarcomas are not staged using this staging system. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: POLR3K Gene

value.value: This gene is involved in the transcription of DNA into small RNAs.

label.value: POLR3K wt Allele

value.value: Human POLR3K wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 16p13.3 and is approximately 7 kb in length. This allele, which encodes DNA-directed RNA polymerase III subunit RPC10 protein, plays a role in the synthesis of small RNAs and in immunity.

label.value: Stage 0 Gallbladder Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage 0 includes: Tis, N0, M0. Tis: Carcinoma in situ. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage I Gallbladder Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage I includes: T1, N0, M0. T1: Tumor invading the lamina propria or muscular layer. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage II Gallbladder Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage II includes: IIA: T2a, N0, M0; IIB: T2b, N0, M0. T2a: Tumor invading the perimuscular connective tissue on the peritoneal side, without involvement of the serosa (visceral peritoneum). T2b: Tumor invading the perimuscular connective tissue on the hepatic side, with no extension into the liver. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: DNA-Directed RNA Polymerase III Subunit RPC10

value.value: DNA-directed RNA polymerase III subunit RPC10 (108 aa, ~12 kDa) is encoded by the human POLR3K gene. This protein is involved in innate immunity and small RNA synthesis.
A chromosome band present on 9q

label.value: Stage IIA Gallbladder Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIA includes: T2a, N0, M0. T2a: Tumor invading the perimuscular connective tissue on the peritoneal side, without involvement of the serosa (visceral peritoneum). N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIB Gallbladder Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIB includes: T2b, N0, M0. T2b: Tumor invading the perimuscular connective tissue on the hepatic side, with no extension into the liver. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage III Gallbladder Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage III includes: IIIA: (T3, N0, M0); IIIB: (T1-3, N1, M0). T1: Tumor invading the lamina propria or muscular layer. T2: Tumor invading the perimuscular connective tissue on the peritoneal side, without involvement of the serosa (visceral peritoneum); or tumor invading the perimuscular connective tissue on the hepatic side, with no extension into the liver. T3: Tumor perforating the serosa (visceral peritoneum) and/or directly invading the liver and/or one other adjacent organ or structure, such as the stomach, duodenum, colon, pancreas, omentum, or extrahepatic bile ducts. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. N1: Metastases to one to three regional lymph nodes. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIA Gallbladder Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIIA includes: T3, N0, M0. T3: Tumor perforating the serosa (visceral peritoneum) and/or directly invading the liver and/or one other adjacent organ or structure, such as the stomach, duodenum, colon, pancreas, omentum, or extrahepatic bile ducts. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIB Gallbladder Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIIB includes: T1-3, N1, M0. T1: Tumor invading the lamina propria or muscular layer. T2: Tumor invading the perimuscular connective tissue on the peritoneal side, without involvement of the serosa (visceral peritoneum); or tumor invading the perimuscular connective tissue on the hepatic side, with no extension into the liver. T3: Tumor perforating the serosa (visceral peritoneum) and/or directly invading the liver and/or one other adjacent organ or structure, such as the stomach, duodenum, colon, pancreas, omentum, or extrahepatic bile ducts. N1: Metastases to one to three regional lymph nodes. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IV Gallbladder Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IV includes: IVA: T4, N0-1, M0; IVB: (Any T, N2, M0); (Any T, Any N, M1). T4: Tumor invading the main portal vein or hepatic artery or invading two or more extrahepatic organs or structures. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. N1: Metastases to one to three regional lymph nodes. N2: Metastases to four or more regional lymph nodes. M0: No distant metastasis. M1: Distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IVA Gallbladder Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IVA includes: T4, N0-1, M0. T4: Tumor invading the main portal vein or hepatic artery or invading two or more extrahepatic organs or structures. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. N1: Metastases to one to three regional lymph nodes. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)
